The paper deals with scene parsing, which is a computer vision task, and proposes a new network architecture to improve the performance of scene parsing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces two transform units to learn pixel-level consensus features, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a data-driven approach to learn features, which falls under the scope of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with semantic categories and features, which are related to natural language processing, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with image datasets, which is related to multimedia, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another possible sub-category.
